<div class="container mt-4 mb-4">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
      
      <p class="lead">This Cookie Policy explains how <%= host_platform.name %> uses cookies and similar technologies to recognize you when you visit our platform.</p>
      
      <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 20, 2025</p>

      <nav class="my-4">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#what-are-cookies">What Are Cookies?</a></li>
          <li><a href="#why-we-use-cookies">Why We Use Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#types-of-cookies">Types of Cookies We Use</a></li>
          <li><a href="#essential-cookies">Essential Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#optional-cookies">Optional Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#your-choices">Your Choices Regarding Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#cookie-management">How to Manage Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#privacy-laws">Canadian and International Privacy Laws</a></li>
          <li><a href="#contact">Contact Us</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <h2 id="what-are-cookies">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
      
      <p>Cookies are small data files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. Cookies are widely used by website owners in order to make their websites work, or to work more efficiently, as well as to provide reporting information.</p>
      
      <p>Cookies set by the website owner (in this case, <%= host_platform.name %>) are called "first-party cookies." Cookies set by parties other than the website owner are called "third-party cookies." Community Engine relies on first-party cookies for session, security, and basic platform functionality. A host may add third-party services separately, but those are not part of the default Community Engine cookie model.</p>

      <h2 id="why-we-use-cookies">2. Why We Use Cookies</h2>
      
      <p>We use cookies primarily for technical reasons that are necessary for the platform to operate. These are "essential" or "strictly necessary" cookies. Community Engine also includes internal, privacy-focused metrics, but those metrics do not rely on cookies by default.</p>

      <h2 id="types-of-cookies">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

      <h3>First-Party Cookies (Always Active)</h3>
      <p>These are cookies that we set ourselves. We use these cookies to provide our core services and functionality.</p>

      <h3>Third-Party Cookies (Host-Specific)</h3>
      <p>Some hosts may add third-party services to their own platform deployment. If that happens, those services may set cookies or similar browser storage. Those integrations are host-specific and should be described in the host's own privacy and cookie disclosures.</p>

      <h2 id="essential-cookies">4. Essential Cookies</h2>
      
      <p>These cookies are strictly necessary to provide you with services available through our platform and to use some of its features. Because these cookies are strictly necessary to deliver the platform, you cannot refuse them without impacting how our platform functions. You can block or delete them by changing your browser settings as described below under "Your Choices Regarding Cookies."</p>

      <div class="table-responsive my-4">
        <table class="table table-bordered">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Cookie Name</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
              <th>Type</th>
              <th>Duration</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>_better_together_session</code></td>
              <td>Maintains your login session and stores temporary data like invitation tokens, locale preferences, and debug settings</td>
              <td>First-party</td>
              <td>Session (6 hours of inactivity)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>remember_user_token</code></td>
              <td>Keeps you logged in when you select "Remember me" during sign-in</td>
              <td>First-party</td>
              <td>2 weeks</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>_csrf_token</code></td>
              <td>Security token that protects against Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) attacks</td>
              <td>First-party</td>
              <td>Session</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3>Session Storage</h3>
      <p>In addition to cookies, we store the following information in your browser's session storage:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Platform Invitation Token:</strong> Temporary token for processing platform invitations (30 minutes)</li>
        <li><strong>Event Invitation Token:</strong> Temporary token for processing event invitations (24 hours)</li>
        <li><strong>Locale Preference:</strong> Your selected language for the platform interface</li>
        <li><strong>Stimulus Debug Mode:</strong> Developer debugging flag (30 minutes, only if enabled)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="optional-cookies">5. Optional Cookies</h2>

      <p>Community Engine does not include optional analytics or advertising cookies by default. If a host adds third-party services that use cookies, that host is responsible for providing the appropriate notices, choices, and consent mechanisms required by law.</p>

      <h3>Built-In Metrics</h3>
      <p>The platform includes built-in metrics functionality that tracks usage patterns <strong>without identifying individual users</strong>. This system is privacy-focused and does not use cookies to perform its default event tracking.</p>

      <h3>Host-Added Services</h3>
      <p>A host may add services such as error monitoring, analytics, or other external integrations. Those services are not enabled by default in Community Engine, and any cookies or browser storage they use should be disclosed by the host operating the specific platform you are using.</p>

      <h2 id="your-choices">6. Your Choices Regarding Cookies</h2>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>Essential cookies are necessary for the platform to function properly. While you can configure your browser to block these cookies, doing so will prevent you from using many features of the platform, including signing in and maintaining your session.</p>

      <h3>Host-Added Optional Services</h3>
      <p>If a host has added optional third-party services, your choices will depend on how that host has implemented them. Any additional controls for those services should be explained by the host operating the specific platform you are using.</p>

      <p>You can always use your browser settings to block or delete cookies, subject to the warning above that blocking essential cookies may prevent the platform from working correctly.</p>

      <h2 id="cookie-management">7. How to Manage Cookies</h2>

      <h3>Browser Cookie Settings</h3>
      <p>You can set or amend your web browser controls to accept or refuse cookies. If you choose to reject cookies, you may still use our platform though your access to some functionality and areas may be restricted. The method for disabling cookies varies by browser and device. Please consult your browser's help documentation for specific instructions:</p>
      
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chrome</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Firefox</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-and-website-data-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Safari</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://help.opera.com/en/latest/web-preferences/#cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Opera</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Mobile Device Cookie Management</h3>
      <p>Most mobile devices allow you to control cookies through their settings. Please refer to your device manufacturer's instructions for specific guidance.</p>

      <h2 id="privacy-laws">8. Canadian and International Privacy Laws</h2>

      <h3>Canadian Privacy Law Compliance (PIPEDA)</h3>

      <p>This Cookie Policy is part of our compliance with Canada's Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA). Under PIPEDA:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Essential cookies are used because they are necessary for the platform to function. If a host adds optional third-party cookies, that host is responsible for obtaining any consent required by law</li>
        <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> We clearly identify why we use cookies and how they support platform functionality</li>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> You have the right to access information about what cookies we use and how they collect data about you</li>
        <li><strong>Withdrawal:</strong> You can limit or delete cookies using your browser settings. Host-added optional services may provide additional controls if the host implements them</li>
        <li><strong>Safeguards:</strong> We implement appropriate security measures to protect data collected through cookies</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Your Rights:</strong> Under PIPEDA, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Know what personal information we collect through cookies and why</li>
        <li>Access information about our cookie practices</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for optional cookies (essential cookies are required for platform operation)</li>
        <li>File a complaint about our cookie practices with our Privacy Officer or the Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Privacy Contact:</strong> If you have questions about cookie practices under Canadian privacy law, contact the operator of the community platform using its published privacy contact information.</p>

      <p><strong>Filing a Complaint:</strong> You may file complaints with the Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Website: <a href="https://www.priv.gc.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.priv.gc.ca</a></li>
        <li>Phone: 1-800-282-1376 (toll-free) or (819) 994-5444</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 id="gdpr-rights">GDPR Rights (European Economic Area)</h3>

      <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have certain data protection rights. We aim to take reasonable steps to allow you to correct, amend, delete, or limit the use of your personal data.</p>

      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request access to your personal data and information about how we process it</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Request restriction of processing of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
        <li><strong>Object:</strong> Object to our processing of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent at any time where we rely on consent to process your personal data</li>
      </ul>

      <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information in the "Contact Us" section below.</p>

      <h2 id="updates">9. Updates to This Cookie Policy</h2>

      <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time in order to reflect changes to the cookies we use or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. Please therefore re-visit this Cookie Policy regularly to stay informed about our use of cookies and related technologies.</p>

      <p>The date at the top of this Cookie Policy indicates when it was last updated.</p>

      <h2 id="contact">10. Contact Us</h2>

      <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Cookie Policy or our use of cookies, please contact us:</p>

      <p>Use the contact information published by the operator of the community platform, together with the related policy pages below:</p>

      <address>
        <%= link_to 'Privacy Policy', better_together.render_page_path('privacy', locale: I18n.locale) %><br>
        <%= link_to 'Terms of Service', better_together.render_page_path('terms-of-service', locale: I18n.locale) %>
      </address>

      <hr class="my-5">

      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        <h4 class="alert-heading"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb me-2" aria-hidden="true"></i>Plain Language Summary</h4>
        <p>Here's what you need to know about cookies on our platform:</p>
        <ul class="mb-2">
          <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Required for login and basic platform functions (we must use these)</li>
          <li><strong>Optional third-party cookies:</strong> Community Engine does not use them by default</li>
          <li><strong>Your choice:</strong> You can manage cookies in your browser, and hosts that add optional third-party services should explain any additional controls they provide</li>
          <li><strong>Third parties:</strong> Third-party cookie use depends on the host operating the specific platform you are using</li>
          <li><strong>Your rights:</strong> You can see, export, or delete data collected via cookies at any time</li>
          <li><strong>Canadian compliance (PIPEDA):</strong> We follow Canadian privacy law for cookie data</li>
          <li><strong>GDPR (EU) compliance:</strong> European users have full GDPR rights for cookie data</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-0">For more comprehensive information about how we handle your personal data, please review our <%= link_to 'Privacy Policy', better_together.render_page_path('privacy', locale: I18n.locale) %>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-secondary mt-3" role="alert">
        <h5 class="alert-heading">Your Privacy Matters</h5>
        <p class="mb-0">We are committed to transparency about how we collect and use data. This Cookie Policy is part of our broader commitment to your privacy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
